cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper presents a new approach to generative modeling for sequences and sequence pairs using a single neural network. It covers a wide range of tasks including machine translation, representation learning, and zero-shot cloze question answering. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper includes experiments in computer vision (representation learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, since the paper uses neural networks, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
